narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot about the Spanish language as well as Spanish cultures.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Could have more speaking and listening exercises in class.

It was definitely efficient at teaching the language and instilling proper grammatical skills. One weakness was that it moved a little too quickly for certain topics, especially those that are harder for native English speakers to understand.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: As someone who had taken elementary Spanish before, the course was not very difficult. That being said, there is a good bit of work assigned (online and written homework every night). The course moves pretty quickly, so there is a lot of vocab and grammar to keep up with. I'd recommend working with a tutor for more speaking practice.
I would recommend this course to another student, as for an introductory language course I believed it mostly moved at a good pace and was challenging but not impossible.
